title: Mainer makes her mark on the high school golf green
text:
Mainer makes her mark on the high school golf green Lincoln Academy's Bailey Plourde is a force to be reckoned with, whether facing girls or guys Post to Facebook Mainer makes her mark on the high school golf green Lincoln Academy's Bailey Plourde is a force to be reckoned with, whether facing girls or guys   wcsh6.com: http://on.wcsh6.com/1RwNx0n   Join the Conversation To   Mainer makes her mark on the high school golf green Maine girl golfer makes her mark on the green. Jessica Gagne, WCSH 7:46 p.m. EDT October 8, 2015 Bailey Plourde CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
WALPOLE, Maine (NEWS CENTER) -- Many think of golf as a male-dominant sport, but one girl from Maine is proving she can hang with the guys on the green. 
Bailey Plourde of Lincoln Academy won the individual girl's state title her freshmen year, and placed 3rd overall in the Maine Women's amateur tournament in 2014. So far this season, she hasn't lost a head to head match on her high school team. Read or Share this story: http://on.wcsh6.com/1RwNx0n TOP VIDEOS
